OL,3,CPlaid Cymru pledges to cut tax for
OL,4,Csmall businesses
OL,6,FHe told members that a Plaid Cymru
OL,7,FWelsh Government would look to change
OL,8,Fthe way businesses are taxed, which
OL,9,Fwould involve reducing rates for
OL,10,Findependent businesses in retail,
OL,11,Fleisure and hospitality, and ensuring
OL,12,Fthat "those who can afford to pay
OL,13,Fcontribute more."
OL,15,FHe told ITV Wales, "For example,
OL,16,Fthere's a small independent coffee
OL,17,Fshop in Bridgend: locally owned,
OL,18,Flocally run, buys local produce.
